<title>AUSTRALIA: RTRS-BT takes stake in Golden Valley.</title>
<headline>RTRS-BT takes stake in Golden Valley.</headline>
<dateline>PERTH 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Gold Valley Mines NL said on Wednesday that Bankers Trust Australia Ltd held 77 million shares in the company as of January 17, equal to 12.98 percent of the issued share capital.</p>
<p>Golden Valley holds a technicial assistance and finance agreement with PT Krueng Gasui of Indonesia, which is involved in the dispute over ownership to parts of the Busang gold deposit in Kalimantan, potentially one of the world's largest.</p>
<p>Busang is estimated to contain at least 57 million ounces of gold worth over US$21 billion at current gold prices.</p>
<p>-- Sydney Newsroom 61-2 9373-1800</p>
